{
 "name": "RPlog_Subtlety",
 "title": "Subtlety",
 "summary": "In the austere corridor of the Imperial Embassy, the bounty-hunter guildmaster Taggor Bren arrives seeking the absent Ambassador to make arrangements for one of his hunters. He is intercepted by the cold, controlled Imperial Count Joir, who tests him with guarded questions before the two recognize one another's roles. Joir explains that the target, Aly, is always shielded by Starshield Marines and asks whether Taggor's hunters can overcome them. Taggor counters that brute force is not always best and -- revealing a past association with the mark -- proposes a quieter approach of getting close enough to stun or drug her. Joir, who has come to value subtlety, is intrigued and invites Taggor to develop the plan.",
